title: Ambient Air Monitoring Sites, Florida, 2005
name: Ambient Air Monitoring Sites, Florida, 2005
description:
Ambient air monitoring sites are point locations with monitoring equipment, and possibly meteorological instruments, that monitor outdoor, near ground level criteria pollutant concentration levels.  
Purpose: Ambient air monitoring data are provided to the EPA, to meet federal requirements, and to communicate air quality to other levels of government, air monitoring
